cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is about a library that provides optimized implementations for deep learning primitives, specifically for GPUs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since convolutional networks are mentioned as an example. The paper also discusses the difficulty of optimizing kernels for parallel architectures, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the library is designed to improve performance and memory usage, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
